  "description": "Bandoneon in push mode — bright, forward, the jubilant side of tango that Piazzolla found in the milonga rhythm. High velocity triggers the push bank: triangle-saw blend that cuts through any mix. Moderate buzz for warm reed saturation. Fast LFO2 on the filter creates the rhythmic pumping urgency of a milonga band at full tempo. Play hard for push energy; soft touch reveals the darker pull bank beneath.",
